    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically sound 2004 BMW M3, a quintessential example of the E46 platform. Under the hood, the S54 3.2L straight-six delivers linear power up to its 8,000 RPM redline, benefiting from a recently serviced VANOS system and documented valve adjustment. The chassis has been proactively addressed with rear subframe reinforcement, ensuring structural integrity under high torque loads. Power is delivered through a crisp Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a factory limited-slip differential. The suspension geometry remains tight, featuring refreshed bushings that preserve the communicative steering rack and balanced weight distribution. This is a well-maintained enthusiast's vehicle that prioritizes drivetrain health and analog performance.",
